%N A378386 Area of the unique primitive Pythagorean triple whose inradius is A002315(n) and such that its long leg and its hypotenuse are consecutive natural numbers.
%D A378386 Miguel Ángel Pérez García-Ortega, José Manuel Sánchez Muñoz and José Miguel Blanco Casado, El Libro de las Ternas Pitagóricas, Preprint 2024.
%H A378386 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A378386/b378386.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200</a>
%H A378386 <a href="/index/Rec#order_07">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (239,-8365,48995,-48995,8365,-239,1).
%F A378386 a(n) = A377725(n) * A385977(n) / 2.
%F A378386 a(n) = A002315(n)*(A002315(n) + 1)*(2*A002315(n) + 1).
%F A378386 G.f.: 6*(1 - 99*x - 1274*x^2 + 8126*x^3 - 391*x^4 - 91*x^5)/((1 - x)*(1 - 198*x + x^2)*(1 - 34*x + x^2)*(1 - 6*x + x^2)). - _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 16 2025
%e A378386 For n=1, the short leg is A377725(1) = 15 and the long leg is A385977(1) = 112 so the area is then a(1) = (15 * 112)/2 = 840.
%t A378386 d[n_]:=d[n]=Module[{r},r=((1+Sqrt[2])^(2n+1)-(Sqrt[2]-1)^(2n+1))/2;{r(r+1)(2r+1)}];areas={};Do[areas=Join[areas,FullSimplify[d[n]]],{n,0,17}];areas
%o A378386 (PARI) a(n)=my(t=polcoef((1 + x)/(1 - 6*x + x^2) + O(x*x^n), n)); t*(t + 1)*(2*t+1); \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 16 2025
